mappings.name: Deletes the breakpoint from the debuggee.

schema.description: A generic empty message that you can re-use to avoid defining duplicated empty messages in your APIs. A typical example is to use it as the request or the response type of an API method. For instance: service Foo { rpc Bar(google.protobuf.Empty) returns (google.protobuf.Empty); }

mappings.name: Sets the breakpoint to the debuggee.
Lists all breakpoints for the debuggee.

breakpoints.description: List of breakpoints matching the request. The fields `id` and `location` are guaranteed to be set on each breakpoint. The fields: `stack_frames`, `evaluated_expressions` and `variable_table` are cleared on each breakpoint regardless of its status.

nextWaitToken.description: A wait token that can be used in the next call to `list` (REST) or `ListBreakpoints` (RPC) to block until the list of breakpoints has changes.

mappings.name: Lists all the debuggees that the user has access to.

debuggees.description: List of debuggees accessible to the calling user. The fields `debuggee.id` and `description` are guaranteed to be set. The `description` field is a human readable field provided by agents and can be displayed to users.

breakpoints.description: List of all active breakpoints. The fields `id` and `location` are guaranteed to be set on each breakpoint.

nextWaitToken.description: A token that can be used in the next method call to block until the list of breakpoints changes.

waitExpired.description: If set to `true`, indicates that there is no change to the list of active breakpoints and the server-selected timeout has expired. The `breakpoints` field would be empty and should be ignored.
